"Consider a company selling a product at a price $p$ per unit. The cost of producing each unit is $c$. The company aims to sell exactly $n$ units in order to make a profit, defined as the difference between revenue ($rp$) and production cost ($cp$). Find an expression for the price per unit that maximizes this profit.

II. Mathematical Formulation
\boxed{\text{Maximize }rp- cp = (pn)p - nc \quad \text{(1)}\quad \text{subject to}\quad np=n}

III. Purchase and Solution
"In the context of this problem, we can reinterpret the target number of units sold ($n$) as the inventory level that the company wishes to maintain. With this interpretation, our objective function becomes:
\boxed{\text{Maximize }rp- cp = pn - nc \quad \text{(1)}}

"To maximize this profit function, we need to find the value of $p$ that makes $pn-nc$ as large as possible. Solving for $p$, we have:
\begin{align*}
np&=n \\
pn-nc &= \text{maximal} \\
pn-(n)c &= \text{maximal}\\
p\left(n-\frac{c}{p}\right)&= \text{maximal}\\
p & = \boxed{\frac{n}{n-\frac{c}{p}}} \quad \text{(2)}
\end{align*}

IV. Python Function Implementation
